               <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="card-text">
                          <li>Date of Birth:&nbsp;{{data.dob}}</li>
                          <li>Weight:&nbsp;{{data.weight}}&nbsp;kg</li>
                          <li>Height:&nbsp;{{data.height}}&nbsp;m</li>
                      </p>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-footer rounded font-weight-bold border-danger h4">Body Mass Index:&nbsp;{{data.bmiValue}}</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid" id="healthy">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-6 md-5 p-3">
                <div><b>Ouch! You are an Obese</b><hr style="background-color: rgb(152, 21, 55);"></div>
                <p>Your BMI is over <b class="text-danger">30</b> which indicates that you are heavily overweight. Your health may be at risk if you do not lose weight. You are recommended to talk to your doctor or a dietitian for advice.</p>
                                <div class="container"  >
                   <p class="text-center"> <b >Macros to Calories calculator</b></p>
                    <form class="calories" >
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="proteins">Protein (gm)</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="proteins" placeholder="Protein in gm" required>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="carbs">Carbs (gm)</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="carbs" placeholder="Carbs in gm" required>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="fats">Fats (gm)</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="fats" placeholder="Fats in gm" required>
                        </div>
                        <button class="btn font-weight-bold" id="macros" type="button">Calculate Macros</button>
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="macros">Result</label>
                         <input type="text" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="kcal" readonly>
                        </div>

                    </form>

                </div>


            </div>
             <div class="col-6 md-5 p-3">
                 <div><b>BMI Categories based on WHO Data</b><hr style="background-color: rgb(152, 21, 55);"></div>
                 <p>The dashed lines represent subdivisions within a major categorization.</p>
                 <img class="p-2 chart" src="https://d26tpo4cm8sb6k.cloudfront.net/img/bmi-chart.gif" alt="" width="100%"/>
                 <br><br>
                                 


            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
{{!-- BMR calculation --}}
<div class="bg-white"><br>
    <div class="container">
                        <div class="ml-2 p-2 text-light" style="background-color: rgb(152, 21, 55);"><b>BMR(Basal Metabolic Rate)</b></div>
                <p class="ml-3  p-2">Your BMR is the amount of energy you expend each day when at rest.  This Calculator allows you to calculate not only the number of calories you burn when inactive, but also a daily calorie figure that takes into account your lifestyle activity level. </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-2"></div>
            <div class="col-8 md-5 p-3" >
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="text-center"> <b>BMR Calculation</b><hr></p>
                    <form class="calories" id="calBmr" autocomplete="on">
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="weight">Weight in kg:</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="weight" value={{data.weight}} readonly>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="height">Height in cm:</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="height" value={{data.height}} readonly>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                         <label for="age">Age:</label>
                         <input type="number" class="form-control form-control-sm" id="age" required>
                        </div>
                        <p class="font-weight-bold">Gender:
                              <br/><div class="bottom text-light">
                                <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" id="male" required>&nbsp;<label class="l" for="male">Male</label><br>  
                                <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female" id="female" required>&nbsp;<label class="l" for="female">Female</label><br>
                                </div>
                              </p>
                              <p class="font-weight-bold">Please select your activity level:<br/>
	                            <div class="bottom text-light radio">
			                      <input type="radio" name="act" value="0" id="0">&nbsp;<label class="l" for="0">If you are sedentary (little or no exercise)</label> <br>
			                      <input type="radio" name="act" value="1" id="1">&nbsp;<label class="l" for="1">If you are lightly active (light exercise or sports 1-3 days/week)</label> <br>
			                       <input type="radio" name="act" value="2" id="2">&nbsp;<label class="l" for="2">If you are moderately active (moderate exercise 3-5 days/week)</label> <br>
			                      <input type="radio" name="act" value="3" id="3">&nbsp;<label class="l" for="3">If you are very active (hard exercise 6-7 days/week)</label> <br>
                                 <input type="radio" name="act" value="4" id="4">&nbsp;<label class="l" for="4">If you are super active (very hard exercise and a physical job)</label> <br>
	                                </div></p>
                              <button class="btn font-weight-bold " id="bmr" type="button">BMR</button><br>
                              <div class="form-group" id="bmrRes" style="display: none;"><br>
                         <textarea class="form-control alert alert-danger font-weight-bold" rows="3" id="daily" readonly></textarea>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group" id="summary" style="display: none;">
                         <label for="bmr">Summary:</label>
                         <textarea class="form-control alert alert-success font-weight-bold" rows="3" id="dailyBmr" readonly></textarea>
                        </div>
                    </form>


                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-2"></div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="container  mt-5 p-3">
        <div class="ml-2 p-2" style="background-color: rgb(135, 156, 42);">
    <b >Health risks related to Obesity</b></div>
        <div class="container">
    <ul>
        <li >Heart disease and stroke</li>
        <li >High blood pressure</li>
        <li>Diabetes</li>
        <li >Gallbladder disease and gallstones</li>
        <li >Osteoarthritis</li>
        <li>Breathing problems, such as sleep apnea (when a person stops breathing for short episodes during sleep) and asthma</li>
    </ul>
    </div>
 <p class="ml-3 h6 p-2">*Not everyone who is obese has these problems. The risk rises if you have a family history of one of those conditions.</p>

</div>

<div class="container mt-5 p-3">
        <div class="ml-2 p-2" style="background-color: rgb(135, 156, 42);">
    <b >BMI and health</b></div>

    <ul>
        <li><h5>Body fat is relevant, not body mass</h5></li>
        <p>As far as health is concerned, excess body fat is negative. In contrast, an above-average muscle mass is more likely to be positive.</p>
        <p>The BMI does not distinguish between body fat and fat-free mass. Yet statistics show that the body mass index of about 73 percent of the people is quite a significant indicator of the body fat percentage.</p>
        <p>Thus, in three out of four cases, the BMI seems to have a significant relevance to health and in one out of four cases it does not seem to have any.</p>
        <li><h5>Body fat percentage vs. BMI</h5></li>
        <p>Despite its high relevance to health, the body fat percentage has its shortcomings. Scales for measuring body fat are simple to use but imprecise; the more accurate methods are very complicated and require skilled personnel.</p>
        <p>The BMI, in contrast, can be calculated from two simple measurements which are reliable in most cases.</p>
        <p>This seems to be the main reason why the BMI is still the most widely used value for estimating the body fat.</p>
    </ul>

</div>